@csuwildcat I donâ€™t think (1) or (2) should ever be at the Bitcoin base layer.

If I liked that design then I wouldâ€™ve started a separate L1 like Ethereum or Solana.

I think that a durable/simple money layer of Bitcoin combined with a layer for expressive contracts is powerful.

@PrestonPysh @adam3us @fluidvoice @Stacks Yep youâ€™re close to the crux of it.

There are alternate designs like Liquid (federated not open) or DLCs/RGB (offline limited smart contracts).

Fully expressive smart contracts like what devs are used to on Ethereum, Avalanche etc on open networks require gas assets.

@BitcoinAsteroid @PrestonPysh @APompliano @FrancisSuarez As much as I like Taproot (itâ€™s great!) we should not confuse it with fully expressive smart contracts.

The type of contracts enables by Taproot are offline contracts which are fairly limited compared to what devs are used to on Ethereum, Solana etc.

Stacks has full contracts.

