@fuserleer I mostly look at what developers are doing (vs. transaction volumes). 

There is solid data, e.g., stats from GitHub, that shows that developers are increasingly building on new L1s.

Does not mean Ethereum is not growing itself. But â€œghost chainsâ€ is just false.

@WillPow13 I used quotes for â€œEthereum killersâ€ because I donâ€™t like the term.

These are new L1s with novel capabilities and theyâ€™re finding use cases for those capabilities.

Of course, some overlap and competition with existing Ethereum.

