Nodes need incentives to maintain the smart contract state and to execute smart contracts. You also canâ€™t put that state in Bitcoin.

Can hate the token and lose smart contracts market to Ethereum OR innovate on BTC.

@santiagoroel I read your thesis as Ethereum + DeFi will be bigger than Bitcoin. Ethereum is also a SoV (hence no need for Bitcoin).

In other words, most of the action will happen on Ethereum, including the SoV use case of Bitcoin.

In my view, Bitcoin clearly wins SoV and can take on DeFi.

